@@TJvArrow
<TITLEIMG TJvArrow>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Graphics.Shapes
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Renders an arrow of any size in 12 preset directions.
Description
  TJvArrows is a graphical component that can render an arrow in any of 12 preset directions. The
  component is modeled after TShape and allows you to set the background and foreground color.

  To draw arrows you should execute the following tasks:

  * Drop a TJvArrows component on any control that excepts child controls.
  * Set the Width and Height of the component.
  * Set <LINK TCustomArrow.Shape, the type and direction> of the arrow.
  * Specify <LINK TCustomArrow.ArrowSize, the size> of the arrow.
  * Specify <LINK TCustomArrow.ArrowWidth, the width> of the arrow.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
