@@TCustomArrow
Summary
  Base for all arrow controls.
Description
  TCustomArrow is the base class for arrow controls (such as TJvArrow). It provides all basic
  property and methods to set the arrow kind and render the arrow.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TCustomArrow.ArrowSize
Summary
  Size of the arrow's head.
Description
  ArrowSize is the size of arrow's head. The arrow size is the distance between the tip of the arrow
  to the line connecting the end points of the two lines of the arrow.
See Also
  ArrowWidth
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TCustomArrow.ArrowWidth
Summary
  Width of the arrow's head.
Description
  ArrowWidth is the width of the arrow's head. The width is the (largest) distance between the two
  lines of the arrow.
See Also
  ArrowSize
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TCustomArrow.Brush
Summary
  Brush to fill the background with.
Description
  Brush is the background brush to use when filling the components background.
See Also
  Pen
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TCustomArrow.Paint
Summary
  Renders the arrow.
Description
  Paint renders the arrow as specified by the various properties.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TCustomArrow.Pen
Summary
  The pen to draw the arrow with.
Description
  Pen is the pen to use when rendering the arrow lines and it's head.
See Also
  Brush
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TCustomArrow.Shape
Summary
  The shape and direction of the arrow.
Description
  Shape indicates the shape and direction of the arrow. There are 12 shapes to choose from. See the
  help on TArrowType for information on the types of arrows you can draw.
See Also
  TArrowType
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TCustomArrow.StyleChanged
Summary
  Invalidates the control.
Description
  StyleChanged will simply invalidate the control. Internally StyleChanged is assigned to the
  OnChange event of the Brush and the Pen object.
